.%20That%20way%2C%20we%20knew%20which%20groups%20were%20overrepresented%20or%20underrepresented.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20that%20data%2C%20I%20could%20see%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsubtle-ways-women-treated-differently-work-2014-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewomen%20were%20underrepresented%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20especially%20in%20leadership%20at%20Instagram.%20Women%20make%20up%20about%20half%20the%20country's%20population%2C%20so%20you'd%20expect%20them%20to%20make%20up%20half%20of%20leadership%2C%20but%20only%20about%2030%25%20of%20leadership%20at%20the%20company%20was%20female.%20We%20made%20some%20progress%20on%20that%20during%20the%20tenure%2C%20using%20mentorship%20programs%20and%20other%20tools.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2219ff8beb-9daf-43af-b489-cc3ec52e3943%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20the%20most%20common%20misconception%20about%20DEI%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdei-costco-disney-jpmorgan-company-policy-changes-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EPeople%20get%20quite%20a%20bit%20wrong%20about%20DEI%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20But%20the%20most%20fundamental%20misunderstanding%20is%20the%20idea%20that%20DEI%20programs%20put%20people%20who%20aren't%20qualified%20into%20positions.%20That's%20a%20huge%20mischaracterization.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDEI%20work%20means%20ensuring%20that%20everyone%20who%20is%20qualified%20has%20a%20fair%20shot%20at%20a%20role.%20We%20know%20that's%20often%20not%20the%20case.%20Opening%20the%20door%20to%20more%20people%20often%20means%20reexamining%20the%20hiring%20process.%20If%20you%20hire%20internally%2C%20but%20your%20team%20is%20mostly%20men%2C%20you're%20more%20likely%20to%20hire%20a%20man.%20If%20you%20ask%20for%20referrals%2C%20you%20only%20find%20people%20with%20connections.%20If%20you%20screen%20for%20candidates%20with%20Ivy%20League%20educations%2C%20you%20leave%20other%20perfectly%20qualified%20people%20out.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20misconception%20is%20that%20DEI%20takes%20jobs%20away%20from%20qualified%20people.%20That%20couldn't%20be%20further%20from%20the%20truth.%20Instead%2C%20it's%20about%20opening%20up%20job%20opportunities%20to%20more%20people%20who%20have%20worked%20just%20as%20hard%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20harder%20%E2%80%94%20but%20don't%20yet%20have%20a%20foot%20in%20the%20door.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228224b77e-f05a-4f1c-80eb-b9345ed5e3fd%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20think%20businesses%20will%20want%20to%20keep%20DEI%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20the%20current%20environment%2C%20I%20think%20DEI%20is%20here%20to%20stay.%20Fundamentally%2C%20teams%20are%20more%20creative%20and%20innovative%20when%20they're%20composed%20of%20people%20from%20varied%20backgrounds%20and%20experiences.%20That's%20better%20for%20business.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20Gen%20Z%20and%20eventually%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-alpha-no-longer-youngest-generation-gen-beta-has-arrived-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EGen%20Alpha%20enter%20the%20workforce%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20I%20think%20inclusion%20will%20be%20the%20natural%20way%20we%20do%20business.%20We%20might%20not%20call%20it%20DEI%20or%20assign%20one%20person%20the%20impossible%20job%20of%20ensuring%20equity%2C%20but%20there%20will%20be%20a%20culture%20of%20honoring%20people's%20differences%20and%20the%20strengths%20they%20bring.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bd16fdf3-9c1a-4686-876b-fdd4c0cef686%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20husband's%20death%20caused%20me%20to%20rethink%20my%20career%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202021%2C%20I%20lost%20my%20husband%20unexpectedly%20to%20a%20heart%20attack.%20I%20was%2040%2C%20and%20he%20was%20only%2045.%20His%20death%20caused%20me%20to%20fundamentally%20rethink%20my%20outlook%20on%20life.%20My%20corporate%20work%20didn't%20feel%20as%20fulfilling.%20It%20didn't%20give%20me%20the%20freedom%20and%20flexibility%20I%20needed%2C%20especially%20now%20that%20I%20was%20a%20single%20mom%20to%20our%20son%2C%20who%20was%2015.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELeaving%20Instagram%20was%20scary.%20I%20was%20making%20multiple%20six-figures%20and%20regularly%20received%20stock%20options%20that%20vested%20quarterly.%20I%20had%20recently%20bought%20a%20home%20and%20still%20had%20a%20mortgage.%20I%20had%20a%20good%20income%20but%20didn't%20have%20the%20type%20of%20wealth%20that%20meant%20I%20could%20retire.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20worked%20with%20my%20financial%20planner%20to%20bolster%20savings%20and%20diversify%20my%20investments.%20She%20advised%20me%20to%20keep%20working%20a%20while%20longer%2C%20but%20ultimately%2C%20I%20left%20sooner%20than%20she%20thought%20I%20should.%20I%20had%20to%20follow%20my%20heart.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2203d6b1f2-f221-40ec-84a3-67732f5fc2f9%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI've%20redefined%20what%20success%20means%20to%20me%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20I'm%20an%20author%2C%20content%20creator%2C%20and%20coach.%20In%20my%20first%20year%20of%20self-employment%2C%20I%20made%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20what%20I%20was%20making%20in%20my%20corporate%20role.%20I%20had%20to%20adjust%20to%20getting%20paid%20monthly%20or%20less%20often%20rather%20than%20every%20two%20weeks.%20My%20cash%20flow%20was%20very%20different%20from%20what%20I%20was%20used%20to.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20then%2C%20I've%20grown%20my%20business.%20I%20haven't%20yet%20matched%20what%20I%20made%20in%20my%20corporate%20role%2C%20but%20I'm%20confident%20I%20will%20soon.%20The%20creative%20freedom%20and%20creativity%20in%20my%20work%20today%20feel%20priceless%20%E2%80%94%20well%20worth%20the%20sacrifice%20of%20a%20title%20and%20salary.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThroughout%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20I've%20realized%20that%20success%20means%20knowing%20who%20you%20are%20and%20living%20in%20alignment%20with%20that.%20I've%20done%20that%20through%20five%20steps.%20I%20reconnected%20with%20my%20heart%2C%20finding%20my%20desire%20for%20more%20creativity%3B%20I%20restored%20my%20body%20through%20yoga%3B%20reframed%20my%20beliefs%20and%20ditched%20self-limiting%20stories%3B%20renewed%20my%20spirit%20by%20finding%20joy%20again%3B%20and%20reinvented%20routines%2C%20making%20sure%20all%20this%20personal%20growth%20sticks.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbecame-a-single-mom-after-my-husband-died-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739880541000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67ae18716630eb10385c85f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbecame-a-single-mom-after-my-husband-died-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Regina%20Lawless%20lead%20DEI%20initiatives%20at%20Instagram.%20When%20her%20husband%20died%20of%20a%20heart%20attack%2C%20she%20needed%20more%20flexibility%20to%20raise%20her%20son.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kelly%20Burch)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbecame-a-single-mom-after-my-husband-died-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indonesia%E2%80%99s%20JAFF%20Returns%20for%2020th%20Edition%2C%20Expands%20Market%20Component%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739880528000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F02%2FJAFF.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236311510%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Indonesia%E2%80%99s%20Jo