0in%20hospital%20with%20a%20polymicrobial%20respiratory%20tract%20infection.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20had%20bronchitis%2C%20which%20may%20have%20led%20to%20the%20infection.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInfections%20can%20be%20more%20serious%20for%20the%20elderly%20and%20those%20with%20underlying%20health%20conditions.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpope-francis-carlo-acutis-first-millennial-saint-gods-influencer-developer-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPope%20Francis%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20in%20hospital%20in%20Rome%20since%20Friday%2C%20when%20he%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20a%20polymicrobial%20respiratory%20tract%20infection.%20Given%20he%20is%2088%20and%20has%20one%20lung%2C%20he%20faces%20greater%20risks%20from%20the%20condition%20than%20the%20average%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pope%20is%20in%20a%20stable%20condition%20and%20able%20to%20read%20and%20work%20from%20hospital%2C%20but%20the%20infection%20presents%20a%20%26quot%3Bcomplex%20clinical%20picture%26quot%3B%20and%20has%20required%20a%20change%20in%20his%20drug%20therapy%2C%20the%20Vatican%20said%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Argentine%20Pope%20has%20suffered%20from%20respiratory%20infections%20in%20the%20winter%20months%20before%20and%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Fchronic-cough%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebronchitis%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20he%20was%20hospitalized.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20developed%20an%20inflammation%20of%20the%20tissues%20surrounding%20his%20right%20lung%20when%20he%20was%2021%2C%20and%20had%20three%20pulmonary%20cysts%20and%20a%20small%20part%20of%20the%20organ%20removed%2C%20according%20to%20Vatican%20News.%20The%20Pope%20has%20also%20been%20in%20hospital%20for%20various%20conditions%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Fhow-do-you-get-pneumonia%5C%22%20targ