hots%20of%20his%20glowing%20performance%20reviews%2C%20which%20indicated%20he%20routinely%20%26quot%3Bexceeded%20expectations%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bgreatly%20exceeded%20expectations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20something%20we%20haven't%20seen%20before%20in%20the%20professional%20world%3A%20Employees%20sticking%20up%20for%20themselves%20in%20public%2C%20and%20calling%20out%20their%20former%20employer%20for%20misrepresenting%20their%20work.%20When%20LinkedIn%20introduced%20the%20%23opentowork%20feature%20during%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20it%20was%20a%20tall%20order%20to%20get%20people%20to%20announce%20that%20they'd%20been%20laid%20off.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20people%20usually%20kept%20their%20dismissal%20private%2C%20fearing%20the%20stigma%20would%20prevent%20them%20from%20getting%20another%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20began%20to%20change%20in%20late%202022%2C%20when%20a%20huge%20round%20of%20layoffs%20hit%20the%20tech%20sector.%20Suddenly%2C%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20coders%2C%20product%20managers%2C%20and%20marketers%20found%20themselves%20out%20of%20a%20job%20all%20at%20once.%20Some%20of%20their%20CEOs%20went%20out%20of%20their%20way%20to%20apologize%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-memo-mark-zuckerberg-employees-mass-layoffs-job-cuts-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverhiring%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20to%20praise%20their%20axed%20staffers%20as%20great%20employees.%20That%20encouraged%20people%20to%20use%20the%20%23opentowork%20banner%20to%20announce%20that%20they'd%20been%20laid%20off.%20Last%20summer%2C%20when%20I%20spoke%20with%20corporate%20recruiters%20about%20the%20trend%2C%20most%20told%20me%20it%20no%20longer%20gave%20them%20pause%20to%20see%20that%20a%20candidate%20had%20been%20laid%20off.%20They'd%20come%20to%20understand%20that%20it%20doesn't%20automatically%20cast%20doubt%20on%20someone's%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Meta's%20employees%20are%20taking%20that%20realization%20to%20the%20next%20level.%20The%20groundswell%20of%20defiance%20started%20last%20year%2C%20when%20a%20handful%20of%20people%20posted%20videos%20of%20themselves%20on%20TikTok%20as%20they%20received%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-firings-tech-hr-tiktok-cloudflare-employee-morale-bad-business-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enews%20of%20their%20layoffs%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20most%20viral%20was%20Brittany%20Pietsch%2C%20a%20Cloudflare%20employee%20who%20kept%20asking%20the%20HR%20person%20for%20evidence%20of%20her%20supposed%20low%20performance.%20The%20videos%20were%20uncomfortable%2C%20but%20I%20found%20it%20refreshing%20to%20watch%20these%20young%20people%20tell%20%3Cem%3Etheir%20%3C%2Fem%3Eside%20of%20the%20story.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20new%20crop%20of%20%23opentowork%20posts%20is%20enabling%20Meta's%20employees%20to%20assert%20their%20value%20in%20the%20marketplace%20%E2%80%94%20using%20social%20media%2C%20the%20very%20thing%20Zuckerberg%20helped%20supercharge%2C%20to%20counter%20the%20narrative%20he's%20telling%20about%20the%20layoffs.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20we%20can't%20do%20anything%20about%20being%20laid%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Meta%20research%20manager%20posted%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20aren't%20without%20any%20agency.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20is%3A%20Will%20standing%20up%20to%20your%20former%20boss%20hurt%20your%20chances%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffind-job-searching-hunt-tips-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elanding%20a%20new%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%20The%20standard%20advice%20for%20laid-off%20workers%20is%20to%20avoid%20saying%20anything%20negative%20about%20their%20former%20employers%2C%20both%20on%20social%20media%20and%20in%20job%20interviews.%20Ashley%20Herd%2C%20a%20former%20head%20of%20HR%20who%20founded%20a%20firm%20that%20provides%20training%20for%20managers%2C%20acknowledges%20that%20speaking%20up%20mig