iant%20posts%20are%20proving%20to%20be%20a%20good%20way%20to%20kick%20off%20a%20job%20search%3A%20Many%20of%20the%20comments%20on%20LinkedIn%20are%20filled%20with%20warm%20endorsements%20from%20ex-colleagues%20and%20networking%20offers%20from%20total%20strangers.%20This%2C%20ironically%2C%20was%20always%20the%20power%20of%20social%20media%2C%20as%20Zuckerberg%20championed%20it%20%E2%80%94%20the%20promise%20of%20%26quot%3Bconnecting%20people%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bbuilding%20community.%26quot%3B%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20making%20good%20on%20the%20company's%20slogans%2C%20Meta's%20former%20employees%20have%20proven%20themselves%20to%20be%20high%20performers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-low-performers-zuckerberg-linkedin-job-searching-social-media-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739869502000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67afa0b07bb3f854015cfd09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-low-performers-zuckerberg-linkedin-job-searching-social-media-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mark%20Zuckerberg%20dissed%20their%20work%2C%20saying%20they%20were%20laid%20off%20from%20Meta%20for%20underperforming.%20Now%20they're%20clapping%20back.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aito%40businessinsider.com%20(Aki%20Ito)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A49%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-layoffs-low-performers-zuckerberg-linkedin-job-searching-social-media-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22WFH%20has%20made%20everyone%20NSFW%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20working%20on%20their%20laptops%20in%20various%20positions%3A%20laying%20on%20couches%2C%20sitting%20in%20chairs%2C%20laying%20on%20the%20bed%2C%20laying%20in%20the%20bathtub%20and%20doing%20the%20splits%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67acb8c4eb4be2fff9a46262%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0%3Cp%3EDmytro%20Betsenko%2FGetty%2C%20visualspace%2FGetty%2C%20Westend61%2FGetty%2C%20Jetta%20Productions%20Inc%2FGetty%2C%20PM%20Images%2FGetty%2C%20tirc83%2FGetty%2C%20svetikd%2FGetty%2C%20Ava%20Horton%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployees-work-from-home-benefits-as-good-as-raise-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eperks%20of%20working%20from%20home%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20the%20skipped%20commute%2C%20the%20chance%20of%20a%20quick%20midday%20workout%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20formal%20workwear.%20Many%20people%20say%20it%20makes%20them%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhybrid-work-from-home-office-culture-remote-jobs-productivity-happiness-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20productive%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20at%20least%20just%20as%20productive%20as%20when%20they're%20in%20the%20office.%20But%20there%20are%20also%20some%20drawbacks%20when%20your%20office%20becomes%20your%20couch.%20Among%20them%3A%20You%20can%20get%20a%20little%20weird.%20A%20lot%20of%20alone%20time%20can%20result%20in%20some%20lost%20muscle%20memory%2C%20socialization-wise%2C%20and%20some%20slightly%20freaky%20habits%20you'd%20probably%20keep%20under%20wraps%20if%20other%20human%20beings%20were%20in%20eyeshot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnouska%20Shenn%2C%20who%20runs%20a%20workplace%20wellness%20agency%20in%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20undertakes%20long%2C%20involved%20beauty%20treatments%20on%20days%20she's%20working%20from%20home%20and%20doesn't%20have%20meetings.%20She%20does%20a%20lighter%20version%20of%20the%20scary-looking%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.glamour.com%2Fstory%2Fmorning-shed-tiktok-trend%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emorning%20shed%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20trend%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeauty-trend-predictions-2025-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epopularized%20on%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20between%20sending%20emails%2C%20she%20applies%20and%20removes%20a%20combination%20of%20face%20masks%2C%20wrinkle%20patches%2C%20hair%20curlers%2C%20and%20more%20that%20is%20very%20much%20not%20other-people%20appropriate.%20The%20getup%20is%20tough%20to%20sleep%20in%2C%20so%20she%20takes%20advantage%20of%20the%20ability%20to%20do%20the%20routine%20during%20the%20day.%20Plus%2C%20it's%20not%20something%20she%20really%20wants%20her%20partner%20to%20witness%20%E2%80%94%20you%20know%2C%20to%20keep%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20the%20mystery%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20guess%20it's%20quite%20a%20luxury%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Shenn%2C%20who's%20been%20working%20from%20home%20since%20starting%20her%20business%2C%20The%20Yoga%20Company%2C%20in%202017.%20She's%20never%20been%20caught%20masked%20up%20in%20a%20spur-of-the-moment%20meeting%2C%20though%20if%20she%20were%2C%20she'd%20take%20it%20off.%20%26quot%3BTruthfully%2C%20I%20was%20one%20of%20those%20weirdos%20at%20the%20office%20who%20used%20to%20sit%20on%20a%20big%20exercise%20ball%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Bso%20maybe%20these%20habits%20aren't%20such%20a%20non%20sequitur%2C%20but%20I've%20certainly%20become%20more%20shameless%20since%20I%20began%20working%20from%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20five%20years%20into%20the%20vast%20pandemic-driven%20remote-work%20experiment%20%E2%80%94%20and%20about%20three%20years%20into%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-requiring-return-to-office-rto-mandate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereturn-to-office%20battle%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20employers%20and%20employees.%20While%20people%20aren't%20working%20remotely%20as%20much%20as%20they%20were%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20when%20nearly%20two-thirds%20of%20work%20was%20being%20done%20at%20home%2C%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20work%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-hybrid-jobs-rto-jpmorgan-amazon-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estill%20happening%20beyond%20the%20confines%20of%20the%20office%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20time%20can%20get%20strange%20%E2%80%94%20and%20make%20the%20in-office%20time%20a%20little%20awkward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENick%20Bloom%2C%20a%20Stanford%20economist%20who%20focuses%20on%20remote%20work%2C%20has%20found%20that%20employees%20who%20work%20from%20home%20save%20about%2010%20minutes%20a%20day%20on%20grooming.%20It%20can%20be%20nice%20to%20skip%20a%20shave%20or%20go%20makeup-free%2C%20which%20remote%20workers%20do%20at%20higher%20rates%20than%20those%20in%20the%20office.%20But%20it%20can%20also%20be%20a%20little%20gross.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dropbox.com%2Fscl%2Ffi%2Fm0d5rtg202t78ajg91vij%2FAEA_Jan2025.pdf%3Frlkey%3Dvyw029x5by0haq867l529b3fa%26e%3D1%26dl%3D0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20of%20Bloom's%20recent%20surveys%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2073%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20showered%20before%20working%20from%20home%2C%20compared%20with%2085%25%20who%20said%20they%20showered%20before%20going%20into%20the%20office.%20Eighty-one%20percent%20of%20remote%20workers%20said%20they%20put%20on%20deodorant%2C%20compared%20with%2095%25%20of%20in-office%20workers.%20For%20toothbrushing%2C%20the%20margin%20was%20slimmer%3A%2092%25%20versus%2095%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20this%20is%20understandable%2C%20but%20some%20of%20it%20%E2%80%94%20like%20brushing%20teeth%20%E2%80%94%20I%20thought%20was%20about%20oral%20hygiene%20not%20going%20into%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20Bloom%20said%20in%20an%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEric%20Mochnacz%2C%20who%20works%20for%20an%20HR%20consultancy%20based%20in%20New%20York%2C%20has%20developed%20what%20he%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bunique%20routine%26quot%3B%20while%20working%20from%20home%20that%2C%20if%20anything%2C%20sounds%20more%20over-the-top%20than%20underachieving.%20He%20gets%20up%20a%20couple%20of%20hours%20early%20to%20play%20New%20York%20Times%20games%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-times-editor-wordle-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWordle%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20read%20on%20the%20couch.%20Between%20calls%2C%20he%20does%20chores%3A%20washing%20dishes%2C%20dropping%20off%20the%20rent%20check%2C%20going%20grocery%20shopping.%20He%20considers%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bclarity%20break%2C%26quot%3B%20part%20of%20stress%20relief.%20Also%20among%20his%20at-home%20stress%20relievers%20is%20song-and-dance%20time%20that%20is%20a%20no-go%20on%20days%20he's%20in%20the%20office.%20%26quot%3BI'll%20just%20put%20a%20Spotify%20song%20and%20dance%20around%20my%20apartment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20Lately%20he's%20been%20on%20a%20Taylor%20Swift%20kick.%20He%20thinks%20the%20setup%20makes%20him%20more%20productive%20in%20work%20and%20in%20life%20%E2%80%94%20the%20built-in%20time-outs%20help%20him%20do%20his%20job%20better%2C%20and%20he%20keeps%20his%20Peloton%20streak%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMochnacz's%20company%20has%20a%20hybrid%20setup%2C%20and%20he's%20noticed%20that%20work-from-home%20weirdness%20translates%20to%20some%20weirdness%20in%20the%20office%2C%20in%20that%20he%20can%20be%20a%20little%20extra%20chatty.%20Whether%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Bbrain%20fart%26quot%3B%20about%20some%20work%20stuff%20or%20Matthew%20Lillard's%20potential%20return%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscream-7-jenna-ortega-melissa-barrera-controversy-explained-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BScream%26quot%3B%20franchise%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20feels%20compelled%20to%20gush%20to%20a%20colleague.%20%26quot%3BI'm%2C%20like%2C%20hoping%20people%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWilliam%20Chopik%2C%20a%20social-personality%20psychologist%20at%20Michigan%20State%20University%20who%20studies%20relationships%2C%20says%20that%20while%20working%20from%20home%20gives%20people%20a%20%26quot%3Bton%20of%20flexibility%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20can%20also%20affect%20their%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20something%20to%20say%20about%20being%20around%20other%20people%20that%20kind%20of%20polices%20our%20behavior%20a%20little%20bit%2C%20or%20at%20least%20makes%20us%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20vigilant%20to%20stuff%20that%20we%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20might%20be%20a%20little%20less%20likely%20to%20get%20distracted.%20You%20probably%20don't%20talk%20to%20yourself%2C%20you%20don't%20say%20weird%20things%2C%20you%20don't%20randomly%20start%20singing.%20I%20do%20all%20those%20things%20at%20home%2C%20and%20the%20truth%20is%20that%20I%20would%20die%20of%20cringe%20if%20I%20did%20that%20in%20front%20of%20other%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnline%2C%20there's%20plenty%20of%20chatter%20about%20the%20habits%20people%20have%20developed%20at%20home%20that%20aren't%20really%20appropriate%20for%20prime%20time%2C%20or%20work%20time.%20They%20don't%20change%20out%20of%20their%20pajamas%20(or%20they%20get%20day%20and%20night%20pajamas).%20They%20maybe%20start%20happy%20hour%20a%20little%20early%2C%20talk%20to%20themselves%2C%20or%20engage%20in%20levels%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fdoomscrolling%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoomscrolling%3C%2Fa%3E%20they'd%20get%20into%20trouble%20for%20if%20their%20manager%20saw.%20Some%20people%20say%20they%20feel%20like%20they%20never%20take%20a%20break%3B%20others%20say%20their%20short%20breaks%20turn%20into%20extended%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20it%20or%20not%2C%20the%20office%20provides%20social%20structure%2C%20and%20if%20you%20go%20too%20long%20without%20it%2C%20you%20may%20end%20up%20developing%20some%20overly%20unstructured%20behaviors.%20About%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20when%20I%20had%20a%20fully%20remote%20job%2C%20I'd%20go%20days%20without%20talking%20to%20other%20humans%20except%20for%20the%20ladies%20in%20my%20noon%20spin%20class%2C%20where%20I'm%20pretty%20sure%20I%20was%20the%20only%20person%20with%20a%20job.%20A%20while%20back%2C%20a%20friend%20of%20mine%20got%20into%20the%20habit%20of%20working%20from%20the%20tub%2C%20reading%20and%20typing%20away%20on%20the%20computer%20during%20hourlong%20baths.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EStrange%20habits%20at%20home%20don't%20stop%20at%20the%20front%20door.%20Remote%20work%20can%20also%20mean%20people%20get%20rusty%20on%20the%20softer%20skills%20needed%20around%20coworkers%20in%20the%20office.%20It%20may%20result%20in%20some%20awkwardness%2C%20whether%20perceived%20or%20real%2C%20when%20people%20are%20back%20at%20their%20desks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20the%20norms%20around%20formal%20communication%20have%20been%20maintained%20in%20remote%20and%20hybrid%20work.%20A%20meeting%20is%20a%20meeting%2C%20whether%20you're%20in%20a%20conference%20room%20or%20on%20Zoom.%20Messaging%20via%20email%20and%20Slack%20is%20the%20same.%20But%20informal%2C%20spontaneous%20communication%20%E2%80%94%20chatter%20on%20the%20walk%20to%20the%20meeting%2C%20an%20encounter%20at%20the%20watercooler%20or%20on%20the%20way%20to%20lunch%20%E2%80%94%20doesn't%20happen%20when%20people%20are%20remote.%20People's%20skills%20have%20shifted%20over%20time%20to%20match%20their%20environments.%20In%20a%20hybrid%20situation%2C%20perhaps%20some%20people's%20verbal-communication%20muscles%20got%20stronger%20but%20the%20nonverbal%20stuff%20got%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20environment%20doesn't%20lend%20itself%20to%20a%20normal%20interaction%2C%20all%20of%20these%20skill%20sets%20can%20become%20super%20challenging%20activities%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hakan%20Ozcelik%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20in%20the%20College%20of%20Business%20Administration%20at%20Sacramento%20State%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompounding%20the%20matter%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20don't%20get%20as%20much%20practice%20as%20they%20used%20to%20socializing%20in%20group%20settings%20outside%20of%20work.%20People%20are%20spending%20more%20time%20alone%3B%20they're%20not%20in%20church%20groups%20or%20book%20clubs%20or%20community%20organizations%20as%20they%20were%2C%20say%2C%2050%20years%20ago.%20So%20many%20of%20our%20modern%20interactions%20have%20moved%20online%20that%20it%20makes%20the%20in-real-life%20ones%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20rules%20of%20engagement%20have%20gotten%20fuzzier%2C%20and%20that's%20what%20can%20trigger%20awkwardness%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Constance%20Noonan%20Hadley%2C%20an%20organizational%20psychologist%20who%20founded%20the%20Institute%20for%20Life%20at%20Work.%20Perhaps%20someone%20sees%20a%20group%20lunch%20at%20work%20and%2C%20because%20they%20haven't%20done%20something%20like%20that%20in%20so%20long%2C%20they're%20more%20nervous%20about%20joining%20than%20they%20would've%20been%20just%20a%20few%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECody%20Baertschi%2C%20a%20digital%20marketer%20who%20lives%20in%20Minnesota%2C%20feels%20like%20he's%20gotten%20the%20hang%20of%20virtual%20communication%20at%20work.%20He%20knows%20to%20talk%20to%20the%20Europeans%20about%20how%20cold%20it%20is%20there%20(in%20centigrade)%20and%20get%20down%20to%20business%20within%20the%20constructs%20of%20a%20video%20meeting.%20But%20for%20the%20normal%2C%20more%20%26quot%3Bold-school%20situations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20feels%20like%20he%20needs%20a%20manual.%20The%20small%20talk%20that%20takes%20place%20walking%20to%20and%20from%20a%20meeting%20is%20a%20struggle.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20the%20reps%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20the%20construct%20of%20a%20call.%20There's%20not%20the%20comfort%20of%20being%20in%20your%20own%20space%20while%20having%20the%20conversations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20his%20wife%20notice%20it%20when%20they%20meet%20other%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20they%20worry%20ahead%20of%20time%20about%20what%20to%20talk%20about.%20During%20the%20week%2C%20work%20can%20feel%20never-ending%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20hour%20of%20the%20day%20%E2%80%94%20a%20quality%20that's%20self-inflicted.%20It%20can%20also%20make%20him%20a%20little%20stir-crazy.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20weekend%20rolls%20around%2C%20it's%20like%20I've%20got%20to%20get%20out%20of%20the%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20The%20Twin%20Cities%2C%20where%20he%20does%20his%20weekend-warrioring%2C%20are%20a%20two-hour%20drive%20away.%20But%20even%20the%20long%20time%20in%20the%20car%20is%20worth%20it%20to%20hit%20up%20the%20Mall%20of%20America%2C%20check%20out%20a%20museum%2C%20or%20do%20a%20hike.%20It's%20nice%20to%20go%20to%20restaurants%2C%20too%20%E2%80%94%20cooking%20his%20own%20lunch%20all%20week%20makes%20Baertschi%20eager%20to%20try%20someone%20else's%20cooking.%20%26quot%3BWho%20cares%3F%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20out%20of%20the%20house.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%2C%20just%20as%20we%20can%20get%20worse%20at%20socializing%2C%20we%20can%20also%20get%20better.%20%26quot%3BSocial%20skills%20are%20truly%20a%20skill%2C%26quot%3B%20Noonan%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20you%20can%20train.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20worth%20remembering%20that%20something%20you%20think%20is%20awkward%20might%20not%20be%20awkward%20to%20everyone%20else.%20A%20friend%20recently%20shared%20that%20she%20gets%20anxious%20that%20people%20can%20hear%20her%20walking%20in%20the%20office%20because%20of%20the%20click-clack%20of%20her%20shoes%2C%20which%20I%20would%20bet%20a%20million%20dollars%20is%20not%20a%20thing%20her%20coworkers%20are%20up%20in%20arms%20about%20(or%20have%20probably%20even%20noticed).%20Clearly%2C%20some%20WFH%20behaviors%20that%20are%20not%20appropriate%20for%20the%20office%3A%20Premeeting%20pump-up%20time%20blasting%20Katy%20Perry%20from%20your%20speakers%20at%20your%20desk%20is%20a%20no%2C%20as%20is%20wearing%20the%20same%20grimy%20sweatsuit%20for%20four%20days%20in%20a%20row.%20Behavior%20that's%20appropriate%20for%20the%20office%3A%20joining%20coworkers%20at%20the%20lunch%20table%20next%20to%20you%2C%20or%20stretching%20your%20legs%20with%20a%20midday%20walk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20as%20return-to-office%20mandates%20take%20hold%2C%20your%20coworkers%20might%20feel%20a%20little%20off%20about%20the%20whole%20thing%2C%20too.%20Maybe%20it'll%20give%20you%20something%20to%20talk%20about%20%E2%80%94%20or%20commiserate%20that%20you'd%20rather%20be%20home%2C%20doing%20your%20weird%20little%20habits%20in%20private.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-remote-work-weird-habits-return-to-office-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1739869442000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67acb8e66630eb10385c5dcc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-remote-work-weird-habits-return-to-office-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22People%20are%20returning%20to%20the%20office%20%E2%80%94%20and%20after%20years%20of%20working%20from%20home%2C%20they've%20developed%20some%20weird%20new%20habits.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%