project.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2F11-dead-hundreds-displaced-as-heavy-rainfall-wrecks-havoc-in-kentucky%2Famp_articleshow%2F118352367.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2F11-dead-hundreds-displaced-as-heavy-rainfall-wrecks-havoc-in-kentucky%2Famp_articleshow%2F118352367.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Trump's%20Blunt%20'No'%20To%20Europe%20Can%20Change%20Everything%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20new%20phase%20in%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20as%20the%20Trump%20administration%20moves%20to%20hold%20talks%20with%20Russia%20without%20the%20presence%20of%20Ukraine%20or%20Europe.%20The%20Saudis%20will%20be%20in%20the%20mediating%20role%2C%20and%20the%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%2C%20Marco%20Rubio%2C%20Trump's%20Middle%20East%20special%20envoy%2C%20Steve%20Witkoff%2C%20and%20National%20Security%20Adviser%20Mike%20Waltz%2C%20all%20will%20be%20part%20of%20this%20enterprise%2C%20which%20might%20end%20up%20upending%20American%20policy%20of%20the%20last%20three%20years.%20It's%20a%20spectacular%20shift%20in%20Washington%2C%20and%20Europe%20is%20left%20scrambling%20for%20a%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20Ukraine's%20President%2C%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%2C%20has%20said%20that%20Ukraine%20would%20%E2%80%9Cnever%20accept%20deals%20made%20behind%20our%20backs%20without%20our%20involvement%E2%80%9D%2C%20it's%20not%20readily%20evident%20what%20options%20he%20has%20at%20this%20juncture%20when%20the%20US%20seems%20more%20than%20ready%20to%20walk%20away%20from%20European%20security.%20Zelenskyy's%20call%20for%20the%20creation%20of%20an%20%E2%80%9Carmy%20of%20Europe%E2%80%9D%20came%20after%20US%20Vice-President%20JD%20Vance%20underlined%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20perspective%20that%20Europe%20must%20%E2%80%9Cstep%20up%20in%20a%20big%20way%20to%20provide%20for%20its%20own%20defence%E2%80%9D.%20US%20Defence%20Secretary%20Pete%20Hegseth%20also%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20European%20nations%20must%20provide%20the%20%E2%80%9Coverwhelming%E2%80%9D%20share%20of%20funding%20for%20Ukraine.%20More%20interestingly%2C%20he%20also%20said%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cunrealistic%E2%80%9D%20to%20expect%20Ukraine%20to%20return%20to%20its%20pre-2014%20borders%2C%20and%20downplayed%20the%20prospect%20of%20Ukraine%20joining%20the%20North%20Atlantic%20Treaty%20Organisation%20(NATO).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20'Once%20In%20A%20Generation'%20Moment%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20it%20was%20expected%20that%20the%20Trump%20presidency%20will%20bring%20its%20own%20set%20of%20challenges%20for%20Europe%2C%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20complete%20rethink%20on%20the%20parameters%20of%20the%20US-Europe%20partnership.%20In%20response%2C%20European%20leaders%20are%20in%20Paris%20trying%20to%20hammer%20out%20a%20response%20to%20what%20UK%20leader%20Keir%20Starmer%20has%20described%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Conce%20in%20a%20generation%E2%80%9D%20moment%20for%20national%20security.%20Starmer%20himself%20has%20suggested%20that%20he%20is%20ready%20to%20place%20UK%20peacekeeping%20troops%20in%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%9Cto%20contribute%20to%20security%20guarantees%20to%20Ukraine%E2%80%9D.%20Germany%20is%20also%20offering%20to%20do%20the%20same%2C%20but%20it%20might%20be%20too%20late%20in%20the%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20investing%20three%20years%20of%20resources%20as%20well%20as%20diplomatic%20and%20military%20capital%20in%20trying%20to%20fend%20off%20Russian%20territorial%20advances%2C%20along%20with%20the%20US%20standing%20as%20an%20ally%2C%20the%20shift%20in%20the%20tone%20and%20tenor%20of%20American%20support%20might%20be%20disconcerting.%20For%20many%20in%20Europe%2C%20the%20danger%20might%20be%20that%20in%20the%20name%20of%20peace%2C%20Trump%20would%20strike%20a%20deal%20with%20Putin%2C%20putting%20Europe%20at%20a%20perpetual%20disadvantage.%20That%20the%20long-term%20costs%20of%20short-term%20political%20expediency%20will%20be%20borne%20by%20Europe%20is%20the%20fear%20that%20is%20now%20shaping%20European%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Vance%20warned%20his%20audience%20at%20the%20Munich%20Security%20Conference%20that%20they%20should%20fear%20neither%20Moscow%20nor%20Beijing%20but%20European%20leadership%20itself%2C%20he%20went%20further%20than%20many%20in%20Europe%20had%20anticipated.%20His%20argument%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cshutting%20down%E2%80%9D%20unorthodox%20viewpoints%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmost%20surefire%20way%20to%20destroy%20democracy%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20his%20calling%20upon%20European%20leaders%20to%20%E2%80%9Cembrace%20what%20your%20people%20tell%20you%E2%80%9D%2C%20was%20aimed%20more%20at%20putting%20mainstream%20European%20political%20leadership%20in%20their%20place%20rather%20than%20trying%20to%20find%20a%20common%20ground%20with%20allies%20to%20tackle%20regional%20and%20global%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EShifting%20Priorities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20Europe%20and%20its%20security%20are%20no%20longer%20the%20priority%20that%20many%20in%20the%20continent%20would%20like%20to%20believe.%20For%20the%20US%2C%20the%20centre%20of%20gravity%20of%20global%20politics%20has%20been%20gradually%20shifting%20to%20the%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20and%20Trump's%20policies%20are%20perhaps%20the%20most%20dramatic%20manifestation%20of%20this%20understanding.%20In%20his%20first%20term%20as%20President%2C%20Trump%20consistently%20challenged%20long-standing%20alliances%2C%20most%20notably%20NATO%2C%20questioning%20its%20relevance%20and%20urging%20European%20nations%20to%20increase%20their%20defence%20spending.%20His%20%E2%80%9CAmerica%20First%E2%80%9D%20policy%20emphasised%20a%20transactional%20view%20of%20international%20relations%2C%20where%20the%20US%20would%20support%20Europe%20only%20if%20its%20allies%20contributed%20more%20to%20shared%20defence%20and%20economic%20goals.%20In%20his%20second%20term%2C%20Trump%20seems%20even%20more%20willing%20to%