informs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EKashmir%E2%80%99s%20chinar%20roots%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChinar%20trees%2C%20renowned%20for%20their%20longevity%20and%20majestic%2C%20spreading%20crowns%2C%20offer%20shade%20in%20summer%20and%20a%20breathtaking%20spectacle%20in%20autumn.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20trees%20take%20150%20years%20to%20reach%20full%20maturity%20and%20height%2C%E2%80%9D%20notes%20Tariq.%20%E2%80%9COnce%20planted%2C%20a%20chinar%20tree%20can%20last%20for%20generations%2C%20often%20remaining%20until%20the%20fourth%20or%20fifth.%E2%80%9D%20He%20adds%20that%20these%20giants%20can%20grow%20up%20to%2030%20meters%20tall%2C%20with%20a%20trunk%20circumference%20of%2010-15%20metres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%229253875046%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKnown%20locally%20as%20%E2%80%98Bouin%E2%80%99%20(from%20the%20Sanskrit%20word%20%E2%80%98Bhawani%E2%80%99%2C%20meaning%20%E2%80%98goddess%E2%80%99)%2C%20the%20chinar%20has%20deep%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F386863%2Fforts-palaces-map-india-royal-heritage-history-sites-travel-adventure-trek%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecultural%20significance%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Kashmir.%20Chinar%20trees%20planted%20during%20the%20Mughal%20era%20and%20the%20Dogra%20dynasty%2C%20some%20dating%20back%20to%20the%20time%20of%20Lal%20Ded%2C%20are%20a%20testament%20to%20this%20history.%20Mughal%20emperor%20Akbar%2C%20for%20example%2C%20planted%20an%20estimated%201%2C200%20trees%20at%20Naseem%20Bagh%2C%20near%20Dal%20Lake%20and%20the%20Hazratbal%20shrine%2C%20a%20portion%20of%20which%20still%20stands%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201